Thais, by this time, is informed of Pamphila’s missortune: and in- quiring of Pythias, who is willing to palliate matters, is answered only by evasions. Thais, therefore, comes here upon the stage, in a passion with Pythias, and chides her for her shuffling replies. At last, after some discourse, Chaerea discovers himself coming from Antipho’s, where he had not an opportunity of changing his dress.
